!
! TABULATED QUANTITIES, TOTAL OF 2657 SOURCES
!
!   NO ............ Source running number ....................................
!   S1 ............ Number of the smallest scale where source first appears ..
!   S2 ............ Number of the largest scale where source still exists ....
!   SX ............ Number of the footprinting scale for current source ......
!   XCO_P ......... X-coordinate relative to the lower-left pixel (1,1) ...... (pixels)
!   YCO_P ......... Y-coordinate relative to the lower-left pixel (1,1) ...... (pixels)
!   WCS_ACOOR ..... WCS (J2000) alpha-coordinate of current source ........... (degrees)
!   WCS_DCOOR ..... WCS (J2000) delta-coordinate of current source ........... (degrees)
!   FG ............ Flag describing global properties over all wavelengths ... see definitions below
!   SIGN .......... Global detection significance over all wavelengths ....... SIGN = sqrt ( sum ( SIGNM^2 ) )
!   GOOD .......... Global goodness combining significance and S/N ........... GOOD = sqrt ( sum ( GOODM^2 ) )
!   FM ............ Flag describing monochromatic properties ................. see definitions below
!   SIGNM ......... Detection significance from monochromatic single scales .. SIGNM = SSPEAK / SSTDEV single-scale analog of S/N ratio
!   GOODM ......... Monochromatic goodness combining significance and S/N .... GOODM = (SIGNM / SIGNM_MIN) * sqrt ( SNRP / SNRP_MIN * SNRT / SNRT_MIN ) * (BFWHM / AFWHM)
!   FXP_BST ....... Peak intensity ........................................... (Jy/beam|H2/cm^2/beam) conversion from MJy/sr|H2/cm^2: 4.8538E-03 2.0651E+02 1.0013E-02 3.7532E+02 1.8122E-02 3.8218E-02
!   FXP_ERR ....... Peak intensity error ..................................... (Jy/beam|H2/cm^2/beam) conversion from MJy/sr|H2/cm^2: 4.8538E-03 2.0651E+02 1.0013E-02 3.7532E+02 1.8122E-02 3.8218E-02
!   FXT_BST ....... Total flux ............................................... (Jy|H2/cm^2*arcsec^2)
!   FXT_ERR ....... Total flux error ......................................... (Jy|H2/cm^2*arcsec^2)
!   FXT_ALT ....... Total flux (Gaussian) or MASS ............................ (Jy|Msun) conversion of FXT_BST to MASS (Msun): 1.0927E-26 for a distance of 1.44E+02 pc
!   SCALE ......... Characteristic size (FWHM) or ALPHABE .................... (arcsec) ALPHABE = 2.4 * FWHMSIZE * SOUND^2 / GRAVITY / MASS
!   AFWHM ......... Major size at half-maximum (FWHM) ........................ (arcsec) interpolated from intensities at half-maximum
!   BFWHM ......... Minor size at half-maximum (FWHM) ........................ (arcsec) interpolated from intensities at half-maximum
!   ASIZE ......... Major size from intensity moments ........................ (arcsec) below half-maximum for non-Gaussian sources
!   BSIZE ......... Minor size from intensity moments ........................ (arcsec) below half-maximum for non-Gaussian sources
!   THETA ......... Angle of the major axis (east of vertical) ............... (degrees) position angle PA = THETA - 3.800E+01 (east of north)
!   FOFA .......... Footprint expansion or shrinkage scaling factor .......... "negative" for sources with unfinished footprints
!   FOOA .......... Full major axis of an elliptical footprint ............... (arcsec)
!   FOOB .......... Full minor axis of an elliptical footprint ............... (arcsec)
!
! DEFINITIONS AND COMMENTS:
!
! 1. Catalog entries may have a value of 0.000E+00 for sources outside the observational mask
! 2. SIGNM has a special value of 9.999E-31 if a source is not visible in clean single scales
! 3. SIGNM has a special value of 7.777E-31 if a source has deconvolved peak intensity equal zero
! 4. FX*_BST and FX*_ERR have a special value of 9.999E-31 if their measurements are < 1.0E-30
! 5. Monochromatic S/N ratios can be computed as SNRP = FXP_BST / FXP_ERR, SNRT = FXT_BST / FXT_ERR
! 6. Meaning of the global flag FG:
!     FG = 0 ..... source is isolated: not blended with any other source in any waveband
!     FG = 1 ..... source is blended: footprints intersect by more than 20% in at least one waveband
!     FG = 2 ..... source is sub-structured: its footprint area contains at least one other source
!     FG = 3 ..... source is sub-structuring: causing a larger source to be sub-structured
! 7. Meaning of the monochromatic flag FM: <~ "negative" when deblending iterations did not converge
!     FM =   0 ... source has no problems identified in waveband
!     FM =   1 ... source sizes are suspicious: sqrt ( AFWHM * BFWHM ) / BEAM < 0.95 or AFWHM / ASIZE > 1.4 or BFWHM / BSIZE > 1.4
!     FM =   2 ... source is larger than the desired maximum size: sqrt ( FOOA * FOOB ) / FOFA > SRCMAXSIZE = 90.0 90.0 120.0 120.0 160.0 240.0 arcsec
!     FM =   4 ... source is too much elongated: AFWHM / BFWHM > 2 or AFWHM / FOOA is too close to 1.
!     FM =  10 ... source peak intensity is not measurable: FXP_BST / FXP_ERR < 2
!     FM =  20 ... source total flux is not measurable: FXT_BST / FXT_ERR < 2
!     FM =  40 ... source peak intensity FXP_BST < 0 or FXP_BST and total flux FXT_BST have opposite signs
!     FM = 100 ... source is sub-structured: its footprint area contains at least one mesurable source
!  _______________________________________________________________________________
! |                                                                               |
! | *!*( SOURCES FROM MULTI-WAVELENGTH CATALOGS SHOULD NEVER BE USED BLINDLY )*!* |
! |                                                                               |
! |  Select only sufficiently good sources in each waveband, on the basis of the  |
! |  quantities provided: SIGNM, GOODM, FM, FXP_BST / FXP_ERR, FXT_BST / FXT_ERR, |
! |  AFWHM / BFWHM, FOOA / AFWHM, etc.                                            |
! |                                                                               |
! | *!*(   RECOMMENDED OPTIMAL SELECTION CRITERIA BASED ON BENCHMARK TESTS   )*!* |
! |                                                                               |
! |      abs ( GOODM ) > 1  &  abs ( SIGNM ) > 1  &  FXP_BST / FXP_ERR > 2  &     |
! |      FXT_BST / FXT_ERR > 2  &  AFWHM / BFWHM < 2  &  FOOA / AFWHM > 1.15      |
! |_______________________________________________________________________________|
!
